[
  {
    "title": "Note!",
    "description": "Thats the exact copy of the guide a dude postet on steam, but with checkmarks. Shoutout to them! See the original guide here: <a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3104481630\" target=\"_blank\">Original Guide</a>. Their pictures, not mine. Everything past this block is borrowed.\n\nAlso for some Reason its 201 Runes but there should be 200. If you find the wrong one, please let me know! Discord: derjokko",
    "elements": []
  },
  {
    "title": "Introduction",
    "description": "",
    "elements": [
      {
        "type": "description",
        "text": "A few things in advance:"
      },
      {
        "type": "description",
        "text": "I tried to write the table in a specific order if possible so you don't have to fly back and forth over the whole map, but I wrote the runes you can find in caves seperately, because they require some preperation and even in some easier caves you can't just rush in."
      },
      {
        "type": "left_picture",
        "src": "assets/img/3104481630_preview_20231203122222_1 Rune.jpg"
      },
      {
        "type": "description",
        "text": "You can collect the runes on your mount which makes it safer to get them and this way even your dino receives the x4 xp bonus for the 600 seconds.\nThe rune icon serves only as counter and if you hold \"H\" you can see how much you already got.\nThe icon does not disappear after you collected all runes, so better get used to it."
      },
      {
        "type": "description",
        "text": "I recommend sticking to the order so you don't loose track, but you don't have to do that, this guide is intended to help you and not limit.\nI'm only saying this because you can see how many are missing, but you can't see which ones are missing."
      },
      {
        "type": "description",
        "text": "There are the wikis or videos that tell you the coordinates, but sometimes important additional information about the locations or the caves where the runes are is missing.\nI have collected all runes myself and can provide information to things like rune locations that go beyond what your GPS can display or those that are hidden and this guide should compensate that."
      },
      {
        "type": "right_picture",
        "src": "assets/img/3104481630_preview_ARK rune_floating.gif"
      },
      {
        "type": "description",
        "text": "A GPS is necessary, otherwise the coordinates would be useless, but I highly recommend the use of a Desmodus, because the other realms are treated like caves and some locations are high up.\nAlso the caves of Fjordur are not designed for a pure land mount, so you have to get a Rock Drake or a Shadowmane, a Desmodus a glider / climber or have cave flyers enabled.\nOtherwise you'll need too many Grappling Hooks and Climbing Picks."
      },
      {
        "type": "description",
        "text": "For some caves you will need SCUBA gear, Lesser Antidote, Fur and Ghillie armour for hypothermal and hyperthermal insulation and a light source (preferably a light pet).\nA hazard suit is not needed"
      },
      {
        "type": "description",
        "text": "And that's it, I wish you a good hunt for the runes."
      }
    ]
  },
